Package: catcheR
Type: Package
Title: Plasmid Library Sequencing Analysis for shRNA CATCHER Experiments
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-05-17
Authors@R: person("Elisa", "Balmas",
    email = "elisa.balmas@unito.it",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: End-to-end quality control and analysis of shRNA plasmid library
    sequencing data produced by the CATCHER protocol. Wraps the corrected
    Python extraction script (plasmid_final_corrected.py) and provides R
    functions for single-library QC, two-library comparison, birthday-problem
    duplicate estimation, and publication-ready plot generation.
    Key concepts: Barcode (BC) identifies the shRNA; UCI (Unique Clone
    Identifier) identifies the bacterial colony of origin; DIs (Distinct
    Integrations) is a read-depth threshold that filters sequencing artefacts.
